The main points I have made on Twitter and on @TSTRealMoneyPro over last few months: 1. The market transmission mechanism is broken. Blame passive strategies, levered ETFs and Quants. 2. The market leaders - FANG - face an existential threat of more regulatory scrutiny and

supervision. As their technological advancements have outspeeded regulatory oversight. Expectations of revenue and sales growth is likely overstated. 3. The dysfunction and policy "on the fly" in the White House will begin to impact equities (adversely). 4. There has never
been so many political, geopolitical and economic outcomes today than in the past (many are negative). 5. In a market dominated by machines, buyers buy high and sellers sell low.
